The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for intersection management for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Trust Region Policy Optimization, which is a popular method in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper deals with control of autonomous vehicles, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of a global design objective, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of policies for achieving a specific objective, which is a subfield of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
